work.work-title: When all your mercies, O my God

encoding.software: PDFtoMusic Pro v1.6.5 Build 1B9E7 (c) Myriad - http://www.myriad-online.com

credit.credit-words: Unnumbered comforts to my soul Thy tender care bestowed, Before my infant heart conceived From whom those comforts flowed.
Ten thousand thousand precious gifts My daily thanks employ; Nor is the last a cheerful heart That tastes those gifts with joy.
When all your mercies, O my God
Through all eternity to Thee A joyful song I'll raise; For, oh, eternity's too short To utter all Thy praise!

direction-type.words: Through every period of my life
And after death, in distant worlds,
